# G. Delta Card Standardization (Critical Implementation)

## G1. Replace legacy “capstone delta cards” with universal activity cards
Currently, you have:
- Year sections with “What they do / submit / feedback”
- Plus “CAPSTONE ACTIVITIES YEAR X” cards from `current.y1/y2/y3`

New requirement: **Every activity is a card**, for **all years**, including common core.

### Implementation approach
1. Create a unified schema:

activity: {
  title,
  duration,
  description,
  badge: 'All programs' | 'Entrepreneurial Jobs' | 'Business Families' | 'Venture Starters',
  category: 'Common' | 'ProgramSpecific'
}

2. Build arrays per year:
- `year1.commonActivities[]`
- `year2.commonActivities[]`
- `year2.programActivities[]`
- `year3.commonActivities[]`
- `year3.programActivities[]`

3. Render:
- A single `ActivityCard` component (replaces `pt-card` delta style).
- Color coding:
  - Common Core = Color A
  - Program-specific = Color B
  - Include label text: **“All programs”** vs **“Entrepreneurial Jobs only”** etc.

### Explicit deletions
- Remove “CAPSTONE ACTIVITIES YEAR 1/2/3” as a separate concept.
- Remove reliance on `y1/y2/y3` legacy arrays for display (they can be mapped into the new schema if you want).

**Acceptance test:** In Year 1, every item listed in your spec (9 challenges, client projects, first apprenticeship, skill tracks, camp, coaching, storytelling, reflection, networking week) appears as cards.

